commit.message:
fs: remove debug traces

Fixes compile
README: update some instructions

fs: try to use handles as Inode numbers.

Add a TODO for newly written files.

fs: ensure directories are empty before executing rmdir

Fixes #103
mtp: regularize comment format; document android ops
mtp: drop stray debug print and log import
mtp: add edit script to DO NOT EDIT header
mtp: rename {fetch,send,even}Ep -> {fetch,send,even}EP
Use HTTPS for XS4ALL link

mtp: set fetch/send packet size from max packet size in endpoint
descriptor

Hopefully fixes #130

Tested: Google Pixel 3a on USB3 (Lenovo x250)
README.md: update for Go modules
Add go.mod and go.sum
clarify contribution process
import versioned go-fuse API at v2.

fs: various fixes:

* Setattr output

* Fix and test readdir

* Suppress XAttrs.

* Show default perms, default UID/GID.
fs: use handles as inode numbers
Migrate to new nodefs API

fs: call WaitMount

This ensures that the POLL hack is called.
fs: use MountOptions.SingleThreaded rather than NewLockingRawFileSystem
Use Options.SingleThreaded rather than NewLockingRawFileSystem()
Added methods for DCF file system type
Support for DCF file system
Fix broken Markdown headings

mtp: be more lenient with incorrect size declarations in decodeRep.  

This has been observed in the wild with AndroidGetPartialObject64
calls, on Nexus 5, Android 5.1.1.

Fixes #101.
Add CONTRIBUTING.

Set blockSize to 512

This fixes size reported by du, which assumes blocks are given in 512
byte pieces.
Sanitize mkdir argument for VFAT filesystems too.

Don't swallow runTransaction error return.

This fixes a crash if creating a directories on SD Card with illegal
characters, in particular the ':'. For reasons beyond comprehension,
my test device (Xoom with Android 4.1.2 JZO54K) will actually create a
file on the SD card, which returns the name with ":" when accessed
over MTP.

Fixes #95.

Be liberal with null packets in bulkRead

Return the last packet when a null read is expected. If more than 0 bytes
are received, check this data for CONTAINER_RESPONSE and don't fetch an
additional packet.

Fixes #75.
Fix issue where info was never filled
